From: José Augusto de Lima Prestes <doutorprestes@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 17 May 2026
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Omit reasoning_effort and reasoning_content when thinking="off"

Models like devstral-small-latest reject requests that include
reasoning_effort in the payload or reasoning_content in the message
history.  When thinking="off" the code was passing None to the Mistral
SDK, which serialised it as null in the request body.  Additionally,
messages accumulated from a previous thinking model's session still
contained reasoning_content fields that the API rejected.

This fix:
1. Uses the SDK's UNSET sentinel to omit reasoning_effort entirely
2. Strips reasoning_content from all messages in both complete()
   and complete_streaming() when thinking is off
3. Uses model_copy(update={"reasoning_content": None}) instead of
   the broken exclude= parameter (not supported by pydantic v2)

